GILES/LINCOLN/MARSHALL CO.-OTHER GIC
MASON, James E., Apr. 16, 1809 - Apr. 30, 1852. "James E. Mason- Apr. 16, 1809-Apr. 30, 1852." Stone broken right thru the name and the "JA" in JAMES is shaled off. This stone was found broken in half and loose from its base and almost covered in dirt. I pick up the two parts fitted them together and layed them horizontally - rotated 90 degrees and positioned them onto the base. The parts are pointing south across the head of the grave in the row. I find that is the best way to keep the stone out of the way of the lawnmowers and weed whackers as some of those guys & gals are not careful. That also gets the parts off of the ground so that water drainage is better and the stone stays dryer. 8022/8023/7903 ATHENS - OLD CITY CEMETERY ALIM

GILES/LINCOLN/MARSHALL CO.-OTHER GIC
MASON, James E., Apr. 16, 1809 - Apr. 30, 1852. "James E. Mason- Apr. 16, 1809-Apr. 30, 1852." Stone broken right thru the name and the "JA" in JAMES is shaled off. This stone was found broken in half and loose from its base and almost covered in dirt. I pick up the two parts fitted them together and layed them horizontally - rotated 90 degrees and positioned them onto the base. The parts are pointing south across the head of the grave in the row. I find that is the best way to keep the stone out of the way of the lawnmowers and weed whackers as some of those guys & gals are not careful. That also gets the parts off of the ground so that water drainage is better and the stone stays dryer. 8022/8023/7903 ATHENS - OLD CITY CEMETERY ALIM
